{
  "texts": [
    "For example, the in-medium widths of quarkonia are closely related to the reaction rates used in transport models.",
    "If the widths are reasonably small, quarkonium states can be identified by peaks in the spectral functions.",
    "As temperature increases, the peaks become broader and ultimately can no longer be used to identify quarkonium states.",
    "For example, if the width of the peak is much larger than the energy splitting between different quarkonium states it is no longer possible to extract well defined quarkonium states.",
    "Obtaining the spectral functions from lQCD is challenging because the latter is formulated in Euclidean time, and the correlation functions are given in terms of integrals over spectral functions."
  ]
}